#chocolate

- Have small amount of dark chocolate for blood pressure

Small amounts of dark [chocolate](https://www.webmd.com/diet/video/truth-about-chocolate) "efficiently reduced blood pressure," report the researchers, who included Dirk Taubert, MD, PhD, of Germany's University Hospital of Cologne.

How small is a small amount of dark chocolate? Participants in Taubert's study were limited to 30 calories per day of dark chocolate. That's roughly the number of calories in a Hershey's Kiss.

From <[https://www.webmd.com/hypertension-high-blood-pressure/news/20070703/dark-chocolate-may-help-blood-pressure#1](https://www.webmd.com/hypertension-high-blood-pressure/news/20070703/dark-chocolate-may-help-blood-pressure#1)>

Find brands that are better and don't have high lead or cadmium.
